# Proposal: fix/project-id-test-creation

## Intent

Ensure `projectId` is always propagated when creating a new test plan or navigating between wizard steps. The bug causes test plans to be orphaned (no `project_id`) because: (1) `handleNewPlan` navigates without `projectId`, (2) static step paths in `NavigationStepper`/`NavigationButtons`/`Layout` omit `projectId`, (3) `sessionStorage.active_project_id` is never cleared on project switch, and (4) a stale draft restoring on mount overwrites the current project context.

## Scope

### In Scope
- `DashboardPage.tsx` — `handleNewPlan` passes `projectId` to `/dashboard/plan`
- `ModeratorGuidePage.tsx` — `handleStartNow` back button passes `projectId`
- `NavigationStepper.tsx` — step paths include `projectId` (derived from sessionStorage)
- `NavigationButtons.tsx` — `getTargetPath` injects `projectId` into static step paths
- `Layout.tsx` — wizard nav links use `currentProjectId`-prefixed paths
- `TestPlanContext.tsx` — `clearDraft` clears `sessionStorage.active_project_id`
- `TestPlanFormPage.tsx` — validate draft's `project_id` matches current project; if mismatch, clear draft

### Out of Scope
- Changes to repository layer (no DB migrations)
- Adding new capabilities (pure bug fix)

## Approach

### Fix 1: DashboardPage — pass projectId on new plan
```ts
// Line 475-478 — before
const handleNewPlan = () => {
  resetData();
  navigate("/dashboard/plan");
};
// After: read projectId from same sources as TestPlanFormPage
const projectId = useParams().projectId || sessionStorage.getItem('active_project_id');
const handleNewPlan = () => {
  resetData();
  navigate(projectId ? `/dashboard/plan?project=${projectId}` : "/dashboard/plan");
};
```

### Fix 2: NavigationStepper — projectId-aware step paths
`NavigationStepper` already uses static paths. Add a helper:
```ts
const getProjectPath = (path: string) => {
  const pid = sessionStorage.getItem('active_project_id');
  return pid ? `/dashboard/project/${pid}${path}` : path;
};
// Apply to all navigate(path) calls inside handleNavigate
```

### Fix 3: NavigationButtons — getTargetPath already uses projectId for dashboard
Extend `getTargetPath` to inject projectId for all wizard steps (not just dashboard):
```ts
const getTargetPath = (step: typeof steps[0]) => {
  const pid = sessionStorage.getItem('active_project_id');
  if (step.id === 'dashboard') return pid ? `/dashboard/project/${pid}` : '/dashboard';
  return pid ? `/dashboard/project/${pid}${step.path}` : step.path;
};
```

### Fix 4: Layout.tsx — wizard nav links use currentProjectId
Line 267 — `item.to` already uses `currentProjectId` for Dashboard link; apply same pattern for wizard steps:
```ts
{ to: currentProjectId ? `/dashboard/project/${currentProjectId}/plan` : "/dashboard/plan", ... }
```

### Fix 5: ModeratorGuidePage — handleStartNow passes projectId
```ts
const projectId = sessionStorage.getItem('active_project_id');
const handleStartNow = () => {
  updatePlan('test_date', new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0]);
  navigate(projectId ? `/dashboard/project/${projectId}/registro` : "/dashboard/registro");
};
```

### Fix 6: TestPlanContext — clearDraft clears sessionStorage
```ts
const clearDraft = useCallback(() => {
  localStorage.removeItem(STORAGE_KEY);
  sessionStorage.removeItem('active_project_id');
  setData(initialData);
  setHasDraft(false);
  setIsDirty(false);
}, []);
```

### Fix 7: TestPlanFormPage — validate projectId from draft
```ts
useEffect(() => {
  const currentProjectId = searchParams.get('project') || sessionStorage.getItem('active_project_id');
  if (!currentProjectId) {
    setBlocked(true);
    return;
  }
  // If draft's project_id mismatches current, discard stale draft
  if (data.plan.project_id && data.plan.project_id !== currentProjectId) {
    clearDraft();
    return;
  }
  if (!data.plan.project_id) {
    updatePlan('project_id', currentProjectId);
  }
}, [data.plan.project_id, clearDraft, updatePlan, searchParams]);
```

## Affected Areas

| Area | Impact | Description |
|------|--------|-------------|
| `src/presentation/pages/DashboardPage.tsx` | Modified | `handleNewPlan` passes `projectId` via query string |
| `src/presentation/pages/ModeratorGuidePage.tsx` | Modified | `handleStartNow` uses projectId-aware path |
| `src/presentation/components/layout/NavigationStepper.tsx` | Modified | All step `navigate` calls include projectId |
| `src/presentation/components/layout/NavigationButtons.tsx` | Modified | `getTargetPath` builds projectId-aware paths for all steps |
| `src/presentation/components/layout/Layout.tsx` | Modified | Wizard nav links prefixed with `/dashboard/project/:projectId` |
| `src/presentation/context/TestPlanContext.tsx` | Modified | `clearDraft` clears `sessionStorage.active_project_id` |
| `src/presentation/pages/TestPlanFormPage.tsx` | Modified | Draft validation rejects mismatched projectId |

## Risks

| Risk | Likelihood | Mitigation |
|------|------------|------------|
| Breaking existing edit-flow navigation (handleEdit uses direct navigate) | Low | `handleEdit` navigates to `/registro` without projectId prefix; verify it still works after changes |
| `sessionStorage` unavailable (private browsing) | Low | All fixes fall back to non-prefixed paths if `active_project_id` is absent |

## Rollback Plan

Revert each file to its pre-change state. No DB migration or data migration needed — the bug causes missing `project_id`, not data corruption. Reverting restores the broken-but-stable previous state.

## Dependencies

- React Router v6 (`useParams`, `useSearchParams`) — already in use
- `sessionStorage.active_project_id` — set by existing project-switching logic in `Layout.tsx`

## Success Criteria

- [ ] User can create a test plan from project-scoped dashboard → plan has correct `project_id`
- [ ] User can navigate wizard steps (Plan → Guía → Registro → Síntesis) → each step preserves `projectId` in URL
- [ ] Switching projects clears stale draft → no cross-project draft pollution
- [ ] Back button from ModeratorGuidePage navigates to correct project-scoped Registro

# Design: fix/project-id-test-creation

## Technical Approach

Ensure `projectId` propagates through all test-plan creation paths via `?project=` query params and `sessionStorage.active_project_id`. Navigation components (`NavigationStepper`, `NavigationButtons`, `Layout`) will derive `projectId` from sessionStorage and inject it into wizard-step URLs. `TestPlanContext.clearDraft()` will also wipe `sessionStorage.active_project_id` to prevent stale context on project switch. `TestPlanFormPage` will validate draft `project_id` against current context and clear mismatched drafts.

## Architecture Decisions

### Decision: sessionStorage as project context carrier (not URL-only)

**Choice**: Dual-track — `?project=` query param on navigation AND `sessionStorage.active_project_id` for direct reads  
**Alternatives considered**: URL-only params (brittle on internal navigation), Redux/global state (overkill for simple cross-page传递)  
**Rationale**: Navigation via `navigate()` with query params is explicit and bookmark-safe. sessionStorage acts as a secondary backing store for components that need to derive context without parsing URLs. This matches the existing pattern in `Layout.tsx` (line 119) and `ModeratorGuidePage.tsx` (line 97).

### Decision: Navigation step URLs include `?project=` (not path prefix)

**Choice**: `/dashboard/plan?project=abc123` over `/dashboard/project/abc123/plan`  
**Alternatives considered**: Path-prefix approach would require restructuring all route definitions and breaking existing `/dashboard/plan` → `/dashboard/guia` flat wizard routes  
**Rationale**: Preserves existing flat wizard route structure (`/dashboard/plan`, `/dashboard/guia`, etc.). Adding `?project=` is a non-breaking URL amendment. The `Layout.tsx` breadcrumb (line 267) already uses path-prefix for Dashboard, but the wizard nav links use flat paths — this design aligns with that existing pattern.

### Decision: Draft validation rejects mismatched projectId (not auto-migrate)

**Choice**: Clear stale draft on projectId mismatch, show blocked state when neither URL param nor sessionStorage has projectId  
**Alternatives considered**: Auto-migrate draft to new project (risks data corruption), copy-on-write draft (complex UX)  
**Rationale**: Safety over convenience. Orphaned drafts with wrong `project_id` are the root bug — clearing them forces the user to re-enter context, which is the correct recovery path.

## Data Flow

```
DashboardPage ──[navigate /dashboard/plan?project={id}]──→ TestPlanFormPage
                                                              │
                                                         set project_id
                                                              │
                                         sessionStorage.active_project_id ←┐
                                                              │
NavigationStepper ─[navigate /dashboard/guia?project={id}]───┤
                                                              │
NavigationButtons ─[navigate /dashboard/registro?project={id}]┘
                                                              │
ModeratorGuidePage ─[navigate /dashboard/registro?project={id}]
                                                              │
                                         clearDraft() ────────┘
                                         (also wipes sessionStorage)
```

## File Changes

| File | Action | Description |
|------|--------|-------------|
| `DashboardPage.tsx` | Modify | `handleNewPlan`: derive projectId from param/sessionStorage; if no project context, clear sessionStorage before navigating to `/dashboard/plan` |
| `NavigationStepper.tsx` | Modify | `handleNavigate`: read `sessionStorage.active_project_id` and append `?project=` to all step paths |
| `NavigationButtons.tsx` | Modify | `getTargetPath`: inject `?project=` for wizard steps; derive projectId from sessionStorage |
| `Layout.tsx` | Modify | Wizard nav link array: `to` property uses `currentProjectId`-prefixed path only for Dashboard step; wizard steps use flat paths (existing behavior) — no change needed there |
| `TestPlanContext.tsx` | Modify | `clearDraft`: add `sessionStorage.removeItem('active_project_id')` |
| `TestPlanFormPage.tsx` | Modify | On mount: validate draft's `project_id` against current context (URL `?project=` or sessionStorage); if mismatched, call `clearDraft()` before rendering |

## Key Implementation Details

### DashboardPage.handleNewPlan (line 475)
```ts
const handleNewPlan = () => {
  resetData();
  const urlProjectId = searchParams.get('project');
  const storedProjectId = sessionStorage.getItem('active_project_id');
  const activeProjectId = urlProjectId || storedProjectId;

  if (!activeProjectId) {
    // No project context: clear any stale sessionStorage and navigate bare
    sessionStorage.removeItem('active_project_id');
    navigate('/dashboard/plan');
  } else {
    // Preserve project context
    sessionStorage.setItem('active_project_id', activeProjectId);
    navigate(`/dashboard/plan?project=${activeProjectId}`);
  }
};
```

### NavigationStepper.handleNavigate (line 36)
```ts
const handleNavigate = (path: string, stepId: StepName) => {
  const projectId = sessionStorage.getItem('active_project_id');
  const targetPath = projectId ? `${path}?project=${projectId}` : path;
  // ... existing validation logic (stepIndex <= currentIndex || prevStepValid)
  navigate(targetPath);
};
```

### TestPlanContext.clearDraft (line 111)
```ts
const clearDraft = useCallback(() => {
  localStorage.removeItem(STORAGE_KEY);
  sessionStorage.removeItem('active_project_id');
  setData(initialData);
  setHasDraft(false);
  setIsDirty(false);
}, []);
```

### TestPlanFormPage draft validation (mount useEffect)
```ts
useEffect(() => {
  const contextProjectId = searchParams.get('project') || sessionStorage.getItem('active_project_id');
  if (!contextProjectId) {
    setBlocked(true);
    return;
  }
  // Validate draft against current project context
  if (hasDraft && data.plan.project_id && data.plan.project_id !== contextProjectId) {
    clearDraft();
    setBlocked(true); // forces re-init after draft clear
    return;
  }
  if (!data.plan.project_id) {
    updatePlan('project_id', contextProjectId);
  }
}, []);
```

## Testing Strategy

| Layer | What to Test | Approach |
|-------|-------------|----------|
| Unit | `handleNewPlan` project-context branching | Test with/without `projectId` param, with/without sessionStorage entry |
| Unit | `clearDraft` clears both localStorage and sessionStorage | Assert both storage keys are removed |
| Unit | Draft validation logic rejects mismatched projectId | Mock `hasDraft=true`, `data.plan.project_id='abc'`, context `'xyz'` → expect `clearDraft` called |
| Integration | Full wizard flow: DashboardPage → Plan → Guía → Registro with projectId in URL | Navigate chain, assert each step URL has `?project=` param |
| Integration | Back navigation from ModeratorGuidePage | `handleStartNow` navigates to `/dashboard/registro?project={id}` |

## Open Questions

- [ ] Does `handleEdit` in `DashboardPage` (line 373) need projectId propagation? Currently navigates to `/registro` directly. The spec says "unchanged paths remain functional" so no change planned, but verify `loadFullPlan` restores `project_id` from the loaded plan data.
- [ ] Should `ModeratorGuidePage.handleStartNow` (line 43) also set `sessionStorage.active_project_id` if not present? The current code doesn't — it relies on `navigate` with query param only. No change planned given existing spec scope.

